179static void
180gf119_disp_core_fini(struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan)
181{
182 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->base.root->disp;
183 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
184 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
185
186 /* deactivate channel */
187 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610490, 0x00000010, 0x00000000);
188 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610490, 0x00000003, 0x00000000);
189 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
190 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610490) & 0x001e0000))
191 break;
192 ) < 0) {
193 nvkm_error(subdev, "core fini: %08x\n",
194 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610490));
195 }
196
197 /* disable error reporting and completion notification */
198 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610090, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
199 nvkm_mask(device, 0x6100a0, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
200}
201
202static int
203gf119_disp_core_init(struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan)
204{
205 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->base.root->disp;
206 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
207 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
208
209 /* enable error reporting */
210 nvkm_mask(device, 0x6100a0, 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
211
212 /* initialise channel for dma command submission */
213 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610494, chan->push);
214 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610498, 0x00010000);
215 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61049c, 0x00000001);
216 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610490, 0x00000010, 0x00000010);
217 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x640000, 0x00000000);
218 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610490, 0x01000013);
219
220 /* wait for it to go inactive */
221 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
222 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610490) & 0x80000000))
223 break;
224 ) < 0) {
225 nvkm_error(subdev, "core init: %08x\n",
226 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610490));
227 return -EBUSY;
228 }
229
230 return 0;
231}

234gf119_disp_core_func = {
235 .init = gf119_disp_core_init,
236 .fini = gf119_disp_core_fini,

238};
